The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, August 28, 2004 				 Flexitronics snaps up Future Software
																								Chennai, Aug. 27 (PTI): Flexitronics, a Singapore-based electronics contract maker, has acquired telecom solutions firm Future Software Ltd for an undisclosed amount.																								Under the deal, Flexitronics will buy all the shares of Chennai-based Future Software and make the latter its fully-owned subsidiary, said K. V. Ramani, chairman and managing director of Future Software. The management and all the 600 employees of Future Software will be part of Flexitronics, he added.																								Flexitronics would buy the 55 per cent stake held by Ramani. The stakes held by Intel (13 per cent), IL amp;FS (13 per cent) and the employees (12 per cent) will also be bought by Flexitronics.																								The remaining stake, held by former employees, would also be bought by Flexitronics.																								He, however, refused to divulge the size of the deal. The amount involved will be announced only after Flexitronics get the final approval from the Foreign Investment Promotion Board and the RBI, Ramani said.																								He said the acquisition was part of Flexitronics larger plan to make India its base for the embedded software space.																								Future Software, which has offices in Chennai, US and Europe, posted $25 million revenues in 2003-04. 																								Recently, Flexitronics bought 55 per cent stake in Hughes Software Systems. It also made $10 million investment in Silica, a semiconductor design firm based in Bangalore.
